Endpoints and Parameters

endpoints() returns available endpoints. parameters() include format (internal use only), pretty (internal use only), fields, size (number of results returned), from (index of rist result), sort, filters, and facets. See https://gdc-docs.nci.nih.gov/API/Users_Guide/Search_and_Retrieval/#query-parameters

endpoints()

parameters()

Value

endpoints() returns a character vector of possible endpoints. parameters() returns a list of possible parameters and their default values.

Examples

endpoints()
#> available endpoints:
#>     status, projects, cases, files, annotations, data, manifest,
#>     slicing
parameters()
#> available parameters:
#>     format: JSON
#>     pretty: FALSE
#>     fields: NULL
#>     size: 10
#>     from: 0
#>     sort: NULL
#>     filters: NULL
#>     facets: NULL
